A vintage-style illustration depicting a complex mechanical assembly line inside a factory, where small sealed wooden crates stamped with wax seals travel along brass conveyor belts through ornate Victorian-era pneumatic tubes. The crates emerge from a locked vault with an elaborate key mechanism, passing through inspection stations with magnifying glasses and stamps, finally being loaded into a large steel shipping container decorated with gears and rivets. The color palette features warm sepia tones, aged brass, deep burgundy, and forest green. Steam wisps curl from pipe joints throughout the scene. The perspective is slightly isometric, showing the entire automated flow from private storage to final deployment, all rendered in detailed cross-hatching and engraving techniques reminiscent of 19th-century technical illustrations.
